    The ICommand for removing multiple Items from a set.

    If any of the specified Items does not exist in the set, the set is not changed.

    Leasing:

    • An active lease must exist on the Item that owns the set from which the Items are being removed.
    Authorization:
    • The current user must have the SecurityAccessLevel.UPDATE access level for Item that owns the set.
    • The current user must have at least the SecurityAccessLevel.READ_CLOAKED access level, or the SecurityGrantLevel.UPDATE grant level, for the Items being removed from the set.
    Validation:
    • The Item that owns the set must not already be marked as deleted.
    • The Items being removed from the set may already be marked as deleted.
    • The Item that owns the set must not have been the source in a merge operation.
    • The Items being removed from the set must not have been sources in merge operations.
    • The Item that owns the set must not have ProhibitedEdit associated with its ItemType.
    • It is not possible to remove an Entity from a set if the set also contains a Link connected to that Entity.

      Note: When you issue a command to remove several items from a set, you must ensure that Links precede Entitys in the list of items that you specify.

    • It is not possible to remove Items from a set in the same CommandList as a MergeEntities command.
